sentences: Richelle Ann Mallari Loyola-Avanzado (born January 31, 1979), better known by her stage name Jessa Zaragoza, is a Filipina commercial model, singer and actress.

She is known as the "Phenomenal Diva" and "Jukebox Queen of the 90s" for her first studio album Just Can't Help Feelin in 1997 with the hit carrier single "Bakit Pa?," which became a number one ballad in the Philippines and a top 40 hit during 1997–1999.

She released her album Jessa Sings the Great Musical Icons under MCA Music in 2009.
In 2012, she released her seventh studio album entitled Pag Wala Na ang Ulan with GMA Music.
From 2012 to present, she has been appearing on the weekly comedy show Pepito Manaloto as DeeDee alongside veteran comedian Nova Villa.
This is Zaragoza's return to comedy after the 2001 sitcom Attagirl on ABS-CBN.
